'''Xizor's Palace''' was an enormous building on [[Coruscant/Legends|Imperial Center]] that belonged to [[Prince/Legends|Prince]] [[Xizor/Legends|Xizor]].

==History==
The [[Farfalla skyscraper]] was demolished for the construction.<ref name="CATCW">''[[Coruscant and the Core Worlds]]''</ref>

Being Xizor's primary base of operations, he kept all his files on computers here.

In [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]] [[Guri]] brought [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] and [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]] to meet Xizor, asking for information about the assassination attempts against [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]]. Xizor was the one who wanted Luke dead, and although at first he welcomed the pair, Chewbacca uncovered his sinister role. He managed to escape (something that Xizor intended) while Leia remained prisoner in an opulent bedroom.

[[File:LandoNinja-SOTETC.jpg|thumb|left|180px|[[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]] tosses the [[Thermal detonator/Legends|thermal detonator]] that will destroy the palace.]]
[[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]], [[Dash Rendar/Legends|Dash Rendar]], [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]], and [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] [[Destruction of Xizor's Palace|infiltrated]] the palace through the [[sewers of Coruscant]] in an effort to rescue [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]]. They made it up into the castle, and defeated several guards before being confronted by Xizor and [[Guri]]. Calrissian and Skywalker forced the duo to back down with several [[Thermal detonator/Legends|thermal detonators]], threatening to set them off, destroying the palace.

Xizor retreated, but Calrissian dropped one of the explosives into a garbage chute that led down into the basement anyway. When it exploded, it destroyed the foundation of the building, sending it crumbling down to the surface. Xizor managed to escape in time, as did the heroes.

==Structure==
[[File:XizorPalaceGoSmash-SOTETC.jpg|thumb|right|180px|The ''Millennium Falcon'' escapes the exploding palace]]
The Palace was located in an area of the Imperial Center, making both the [[Imperial Palace/Legends|Imperial Palace]] and [[Darth Vader's Palace]] accessible through protected corridors.<ref name="secrets" /> According to [[Spero]], it was so majestic that it was comparable to the Emperor's and Vader's structures in the cityscape.<ref name="SEnovel">[[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire (novel)|''Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire'' novel]]</ref> 

It numbered 102 stories above ground; a landing pad extending out from level fifty. It had about a dozen levels below ground. The lower levels connected to the [[Sewers of Coruscant|massive sewer system]] of the Imperial Center that had less security. It was not wired for surveillance and relied on guards' reports. Furthermore communication failures happened frequently in some dead spots, because of pipes, conduits and thick heavy [[Durasteel/Legends|durasteel]] beams, a problem the technicians could not resolve. However, drain sensors could report an invasion.

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|I suppose the theme for Xizor's palace would be 'darkly majestic,' kind of evil and sinister but with a regal air about it. For the interior I concentrated on a lot of buttresses, arches, and some H.R. Gigeresque bioorganic stuff combined with Chinese inlaid engravings. With ancient Chinese architecture there are things like flowing lines with lighter contrasting to darker colors and interlocking lines. So I'd do a wall with that kind of inlaid Chinese border, and then below these flowing line patterns there'd be a steel archway with a bioorganic look.|[[Chris Hockabout]], texture artist for the [[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire (video game)|''Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire'' video game]]|<ref name="secrets" />}}
The 3d model of the Palace made for [[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire (video game)|''Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire'' video game]] incorporates various architectural styles such as a medieval fortress with gothic elements, and a "mystical, eastern look". Concept artist [[Paul Topolos]] was inspired by [[Ralph McQuarrie]]'s concept painting of the interior of the [[Imperial Palace]] during production of {{Film|6}}, which however was not filmed.<ref name="secrets">''[[The Secrets of Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire]]''</ref>

